Description: 1988 Fender Stratocaster Plus Here is a genuine American made Fender Stratocaster Plus. The serial number starts with "E4" and the neck is dated to 1988. This is the first version of the Strat Plus with the split Wilkinson nut and Sperzel Tuners. Actual weight is 7 lbs 14 oz.The body is in very good condition overall with no major issues. There are some light streaks and impressions visible in the light on the front and back and a few small dings around the edges. Nothing out of the ordinary for a vintage guitar and no cracks, modifications or structural issues.The neck is straight and the frets show average wear. It's in excellent playing condition with no dead frets or other major issues. The fretboard is clean and the back of the neck has no major dings. The headstock has some small dings around the edges and one on the top. No cracks, repairs or extra holes. The hardware and electronics are original and in excellent working condition. It comes with the original case which is very good condition overall. All of the latches, hinges and handle are in excellent working order and the interior has no bad odors.Please note that I do not set up my guitars before mailing.
